</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB440:v94#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB440"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              440-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Bill
              
                        No. 440</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 262</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">An act to add Section 92.8 to the Streets and Highways Code, relating to streets and highways.</span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Approved  by
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Governor
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">October 03, 2025.
                      </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">October 03, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 440, Ramos.
                          State bridges and overpasses: suicide prevention.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law requires the Department of Transportation to install screening on state freeway overpasses to prevent objects from being dropped or thrown upon vehicles passing underneath, as provided.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require, on or before July 1, 2028, the department to identify best practices for the implementation of suicide countermeasures designed to deter suicide attempts on bridges and overpasses, as provided.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.827901652178627"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 92.8 is added to the Streets and Highways Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_B3162272-7053-4642-977C-A1B44D21D37E"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">92.8.</h6> (a) (1) On or before July 1, 2028, the department shall identify best practices for the implementation of suicide countermeasures designed to deter suicide attempts on bridges and overpasses.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) In evaluating appropriate physical infrastructure, design features, and related deterrent measures, the department shall consider feedback from local jurisdictions and other stakeholders.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Any countermeasures implemented pursuant to this section shall be as determined by the department to be appropriate.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The department shall consult with the State Department of Public Health, behavioral health
						experts, and other relevant stakeholders in implementing this section.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) This section does not impose a mandatory duty pursuant to Section 815.6 of the Government Code.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
